
[1]placid

   PLAC'ID, a. [L. placidus, from placo, to appease.]

   1. Gentle; quiet; undisturbed; equable; as a placid motion of the
   spirits.

   2. Serene; mild; unruffled; indicating peace of mind; as a placid
   countenance or smile.

   3. Calm; tranquil; serene; not stormy; as a placid sky.

   4. Calm; quiet; unruffled; as a placid stream.
